description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Regional Stores Manager to provide overall leadership and management to a business critical function in the Trust.  Our Regional Stores Manager will provide senior oversight to associated delivery plans, ensuring effective financial management and service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new and exciting opportunity to lead a small and friendly team of people, committed to support frontline clinical colleagues, in delivering exceptional patient care.  It will provide direct line management for the Stores site manager &amp; team leader and overall department responsibility for the stores, based across three separate operating bases across the South West.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced manager who capable of shaping and developing individual teams into a single standardised operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a people focused leader, calm under pressure and with the skill and abilities to respond time with a clear problem solving approach to new and emerging pressures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you will be experienced in ambulance service operations and/or stores warehouse and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With current oversight of the Trust central medicines stores experience in medicines management would also be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are excited by what you have read so far, then this could be the role for you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work of the stores team has never been more in focus in supporting frontline colleagues in securing and helping the distribution of personal protective equipment, a range of consumables and other products and medicines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will act as the principle point of contact for liaison with Trust Headquarters and will help develop new and innovative ways of working leading the stores function through EU Exit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you think you are the right person for the role, but would like to find out more, please email jody.james@swast.nhs.uk to arrange a mutually convenient time and date for a discussion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should note that interviews will take place on 26th and 27th November 2020.  It is anticipated that the interviews may take place through Skype.  Candidates should indicate at application if they require support to complete remote interviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is also available as a secondment opportunity.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;*Please note that this role is currently going through the Job Evaluation process and advertised as indicative, and therefore may be subject to change.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
